efficiency: HIGH
time complexity: O(N*M) where N is the number of operations and M is the length of the resulting string.
space complexity: O(N*M) to store the intermediate strings.
energy implications: LOW 
explanation: The solution iterates through the operations, performing the corresponding string manipulation. It builds the final string character by character and returns the k-th character. The time complexity is dominated by the string concatenation operations, which scale linearly with the length of the resulting string. The space complexity is also linear due to the storage of intermediate strings.

